==New Asheville Speedway== The Asheville-Weaverville Speedway is not to be confused with the "New Asheville Speedway", which was located on Amboy Road in [[Asheville, North Carolina|Asheville]], approximately 20 miles south of the Asheville-Weaverville Speedway. This track was closed after zoning ordinances forced the track owners to sell the track to the River-Link Organization, an organization that promoted making the French Broad River area of Asheville a public park.
