{{infobox country at games | NPC = BUR | NPCname = National Paralympic Committee Burkina Faso | games = Summer Paralympics | year = 1992 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Barcelona]] | competitors = 3 | sports = 3 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Burkina Faso]]''' made its [[Paralympic Games]] début at the '''[[1992 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Barcelona]]. The country was represented by a cycling tandem, a [[Judo|judoka]] and a powerlifter. Judoka [[Mathieu Thiombiano]] was also one member of the cycling pair; Burkina Faso's delegation thus consisted in three competitors. None of them won a medal.
== Team == The country made their debut at the 1992 Games in Barcelona.<ref name=":1">[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=BUR&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Burkina Faso at the Paralympics], [[International Paralympic Committee]]</ref> There were 3 male athletes representing the country at the [[1992 Summer Paralympics]].<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=LAUFF|first=JACKIE|date=2007|title=DEVELOPING COUNTRY PARTICIPATION IN INTERNATIONAL DISABILITY SPORT COMPETITION: A HISTORICAL PERSPECTIVE|url=http://assets.sportanddev.org.sad.vm.iway.ch/downloads/70__developing_country_participation_in_international_disability_sport_competition.pdf|journal=Masters Thesis|volume=|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161026234355/http://assets.sportanddev.org.sad.vm.iway.ch/downloads/70__developing_country_participation_in_international_disability_sport_competition.pdf|archivedate=2016-10-26|df=}}</ref> Their participation numbers for Atlanta were one of their highest along with Barcelona. The following cycle, they sent 1 athlete. The country would be absent entirely from the 2004 Games in Athens.<ref name=":0" />
Burkina Faso was represented by a cycling tandem, a [[Judo|judoka]] and a powerlifter. Judoka [[Mathieu Thiombiano]] was also one member of the cycling pair. None of them won a medal.<ref name=":1" />
== Cycling == {{See also|Cycling at the 1992 Summer Paralympics}} In road cycling, in the men's tandem open, [[Djibril Ouedraogo]] and [[Mathieu Thiombiano]] failed to complete the race. In judo, Thiombiano took part in the up to 60kg category. He defeated [[Veniamin Mitchourine]] (of the [[Unified Team at the Paralympics|Unified Team]]) by [[ippon]], in 1:46, but lost his other three matches, finishing joint last of his group. In weightlifting, [[Richard Kabore Issaka]] lifted 100kg in the up to 75kg category, finishing 8th out of 10.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=BUR&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Burkina Faso at the Paralympics], International Paralympic Committee</ref>
