{{Infobox sport governing body|name=USA Cricket|founded={{Start date|2017}}|aff=[[International Cricket Council]]|region=ICC Americas|url=www.usacricket.org|replaced=United States of America Cricket Association|countryflag=USA|jurisdiction=National|sport=[[Cricket]]|headquarters=[[Colorado Springs, Colorado]]}}

'''USA Cricket''' is the governing body of [[cricket]] in the United States. Founded on September 24, 2017, 173 years after the first international match between Canada and the United States,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/20800742/new-american-governing-body-branded-usa-cricket|title=New American governing body branded as USA Cricket|work=ESPNcricinfo|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref> the organization replaced [[United States of America Cricket Association|USACA]] as the governing body in the US following USACA's expulsion from the [[International Cricket Council]] during the same year.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/news/481375|title=USA Cricket launch brand on historic day|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=2017-09-25|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en}}</ref><ref name="times of india">{{cite news|last1=Gladson|first1=J.A.C.|title=USA Cricket getting closer to becoming a new federation|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/cricket/news/usa-cricket-getting-closer-to-becoming-a-new-federation/articleshow/60843288.cms|accessdate=8 November 2017|work=Times of India|date=September 26, 2017}}</ref>

== History ==
In June 2017, the ICC voted to expel the USACA from the ICC, due to issues with governance of the sport in the United States, with control of the [[United States national cricket team|United States national team]] handed over to [[ICC Americas]] until a new board was formed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/19706136/usaca-expelled-icc|title=USACA expelled by the ICC|work=ESPNcricinfo|access-date=2017-09-25}}</ref> Later in the year, on September 24, USA Cricket was launched as the USACAs replacement, as recognized by the ICC.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/20800742/new-american-governing-body-branded-usa-cricket|title=New American governing body branded as USA Cricket|work=ESPNcricinfo|access-date=2017-12-20}}</ref>

== Constitution ==
On December 18, 2017 a new national governing body for cricket in the USA took a step closer to fruition with the formal approval of a new constitution for the sport – paving the way for historic elections in 2018. The Sustainable Foundation Advisory Group (SFAG), set up to unify the cricket community in the USA, has given the green light to a constitution that will see the election of a new Board, including three independent directors, of which one must be Chair.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.icc-cricket.com/media-releases/569234|title=Approved constitution marks historic landmark for cricket in USA|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en}}</ref>

== About ==
USA Cricket is an organization in development that seeks to unify the United States based cricket community and become the sole U.S. governing body for the sport of cricket recognized by both the [[International Cricket Council|International Cricket Council (ICC)]] and the [[United States Olympic Committee|United States Olympic Committee (USOC)]]. Through a diverse Board of Directors, that will be elected by April 2018 and have representation from most cricket stakeholder groups, USA Cricket will lead the sport to new heights by creating and administering value added programs to grow and develop the sport at all levels.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usacricket.org/structure/|title=Structure - USA Cricket|work=USA Cricket|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-US}}</ref>

